Description: Up for sale is this pretty rare Fernandes “The Function” In a Blue Burst finish and a extremely rare Beak headstock. I’ve never seen another one of these guitars with this Beak headstock but I’m sure there are a few out there but there are pretty rare. This guitar has the HSS pick up configuration. This guitar has a internal input jack on the bottom of the guitar (see pic). This guitar has low action and shreds and the stock pick ups sound awesome. The locking nut caps and screws along with the trem arm are missing and are not included in this listing. The Tremolo back cover plate is not original. This guitar will come with a used gig bag to protect it during shipping. This guitar has a licensed Floyd Rose Bridge that has a string through Trem block. This guitar is used and does show signs of being used such as chips dings and finish swirls but nothing to major. The most severe chip is on the front of the guitar on the top bout (see pic) the back of the back of the headstock has some paint chipped away. This guitar is in good used shape for being almost 30 years old. You will not be disappointed with this guitar. Please review all pics as they are part of the description. Please ask any and all questions before purchasing as I do not accept returns. I only ship to the lower 48 states of the USA. That means that I do not ship to Alaska or Hawaii. I do not ship internationally so please don’t ask. I do not ship to PO boxes or APO addresses. I only accept PayPal payment. This item will be packaged safe and secure and insured so that it arrives to you in the exact condition it leaves here. Please review my feedback and buy with confidence. This guitar is in fully functioning condition as are all the items I sell.
